title: Morse 2-5 After School Childcare Program
body: Our after-school program is designed to build children’s social skills and enhance their school-day learning. Children engage in developmentally appropriate project-based learning curriculum, both individually and in groups.

title: U10 League, Monday/Thursday
body: The U10 League is for 3rd and 4th graders. The league helps develop sportsmanship, teamwork, and discipline. Individual teams will establish their own practice schedules in addition to the two weekly games.
accesibility_notes: Coaches speak English, Spanish, and Cape Verdean.
registration_instructions:
Register online at www.samplesports.com/register.

Contact John Smith for team preferences.

title: Cambridge Youth Soccer In-Town
body: CYS In-Town program is for 1st – 8th graders. The game format ranges from 4v4 at the young end to 8v8 for the oldest players. Games are played on Saturdays within Cambridge. 3rd grade and older teams also practice once per week, a second practice is optional.
eligibility_notes: Premier League (1st and 2nd grade as of 9/1/15), Champions League (3rd, 4th & 5th grade as of 9/1/15), Upper School League (6th, 7th & 8th grade as of 9/1/15)
financial_aid_notes: Financial Aid is available. All children within age restrictions will have the opportunity to play soccer regardless family income.
registration_instructions:
Register for 1st-8th grade In-Town by August 15, 2015 to avoid the $20 late fee.
CYS has implemented new online registration, including the option to pay registration fees by credit card or PayPal. 
If you choose not to use the online registration form, you may download a registration form, print it, fill out both pages, and send the form with your payment to: Cambridge Youth Soccer, P.O. Box 390215, Cambridge, MA 02139-0003.
Forms may also be obtained at any branch of the Cambridge Public Library or the Cambridge Recreation Department at 51 Inman Street.
